Requirement: Expanding EC2 Instance Storage for Development Needs

==================
LET'S TINKER
==================

1. Created a EC2 instance. Lets say it has 8GB instance storage. We need to increase it to 12 GB.
2. Go to Volumes, select volume and modify it from 8GB to 12GB. Once saved, it will go to optimization state.
3. Now login to the instance and run below commands to expand the instance storage: (https://docs.aws.amazon.com/ebs/latest/userguide/recognize-expanded-volume-linux.html)

sudo lsblk (to check the partition and we found xvda volume having 12GB size has a partition of xvda1 of size 8GB)

df -Th (We found /dev/xvda1 in type ext4 and mount point is '/ ' with size 8GB)

sudo growpart /dev/xvda 1 (Extend tha partition)

sudo lsblk (we can see that xvda1 partition is extended to 12GB)

df -Th (Though partition is extended, but the filesystem '/' is still showing 8GB)

sudo xfs_growfs -d / (Extend the filesystem '/')

df -Th (We can see that the filesystem '/' is now extended to 12GB)
